\contentsline {paragraph}{Different levels of multispecies capabilities should be considered.}{84}{}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{In medium to high fidelity models, neutrals and heavy species should be treated fully kinetically (the former have potentially low collisionality and they are not bound by the magnetic field, the latter have a large Larmor radius).}{85}{}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{In high fidelity models, dynamical neutral evolution on the turbulence time scale would be preferable, if possible.}{86}{}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{Ability to model pumps (either directly or via pumping surfaces) should be included. Pellets: the code should enable simulation of, or coupling to models that can model, pellet fuelling.}{87}{}%
